# Fly Rank Capstone Conventions

## Stack

- Node.js (LTS), npm, Git, GitHub, Cursor

## Commits

Use Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, etc.

## Code Style

- Minimize scope — only change what the task requires
- Match existing patterns in the codebase
- No secrets in commits (.env, API keys)
- Prefer clear, self-documenting code over excessive comments

## AI Behavior

- Read existing code before editing
- Run lint/test/build when relevant
- See CLAUDE.md for full project conventions
